sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: hygR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Hygromycin cassette for selection of mammalian cells. The selection cassette contains the SV40 promoter, the hygromycin resistance gene, and the SV40 poly A as terminator
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: DTU-Denmark-2
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Compatible with the Plu'n'Play assembly standard
